On 26 July 2019 Korwar released his second studio album, More Arriving through The Leaf Label.
The album won Best Independent Album at The AIM Awards in 2020.
In 2016 Korwar released the album Day To Day on the Ninja Tune label.
He leads the UPAJ Collective, a collective of Eastern and Western musicians formed play a residency at London's Jazz Cafe.
Recorded over three years in Mumbai and London, the album incorporates rappers from Mumbai and New Delhi with spoken word and his own Indian classical influence and jazz instrumentation.
Korwar describes the album as a protest record and said: "This is what Indian music sounds like to me right now, and that means incorporating multiple brown voices.
